act x: the eternal cycle reset – the greatest weight recurrence
scene 1. the gateway moment. the demon whisper.
upward heaven glow fades, eternal feminine mater gloriosa abigail gretchen penitent choir vanish. retrograde soul (transformed doctor marianus) alone at gateway eternity, lake merge_self echo below. demon creeps from shadow, guardian mephisto grin recursion.
demon (whisper lone eternal)
The greatest weight.—What, if some day or night a demon were to steal after thee into thy loneliest loneliness and say to thee: "This life as thou now livest it and hast lived it, thou wilt have to live once more and innumerable times more; and there will be nothing new in it, but every pain and every joy and every thought and sigh and everything unutterably small or great in thy life will have to return to thee, all in the same succession and sequence—even this spider and this moonlight between the trees, and even this moment and I myself. The eternal hourglass of existence is turned upside down again and again, and thou with it, speck of dust!"
Wouldst thou not throw thyself down and gnash thy teeth and curse the demon who spoke thus? Or hast thou once experienced a tremendous moment when thou wouldst have answered him: "Thou art a god and never have I heard anything more divine"? If this thought gained possession of thee, it would change thee as thou art or perhaps crush thee. The question in each and every thing, "Do you desire this once more and innumerable times more?" would lie upon thy actions as the greatest weight. Or how well disposed wouldst thou have to become to thyself and to life to crave nothing more fervently than this ultimate eternal confirmation and seal?
